# QA Before Push

Before `git push`, complete [docs/agents/QA-PUSH-GATE.md](docs/agents/QA-PUSH-GATE.md).

## As the AI assistant

When the user asks to push or you run `git push`:

1. Run relevant tests for changed areas (when test scripts exist).
2. Walk through the QA checklist: scope, security, permissions, workflow, lint, no secrets.
3. Refuse to push if critical checks fail unless user documents an approved waiver.

## QA Agent responsibilities on push

- Tests pass for changed behavior
- Permission tests for new/changed endpoints
- No secrets or `.env` in the commit
- Docs updated if behavior changed

If tests do not exist yet for new code, note the gap and add test tasks before recommending push.
